[{"question":"What do you make of this?","answer":"It\u0027s a tough go for this guy, yes.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":37,"aSentId":38},{"question":"Can you survive if you don\u0027t have credibility and don\u0027t have trust in the public office?","answer":"You tell me.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":41,"aSentId":42},{"question":"He should go, you think?","answer":"Well, I don\u0027t know how you would get up and start to represent your constituents with no credibility and no trust.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":46,"aSentId":47},{"question":"Is it the lying that has made it a completely unsurvivable scandal?","answer":"Neither event is pretty, particular all the photos out there.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":52,"aSentId":53},{"question":"When you go through it though, when you are the subject of headlines like this, what\u0027s it like?","answer":"It\u0027s no fun.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":65,"aSentId":66},{"question":"So, actually, honesty, when you\u0027re caught, is the best way with all these things?","answer":"Everything.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":75,"aSentId":76},{"question":"Would that formula you deployed then for G.E., would that work for America as -- if you viewed it as a corporation?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":107,"aSentId":108},{"question":"Or do you think the actual answer with China is to be more competitive by giving them what they need?","answer":"Out-innovating them is the way to beat China.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":120,"aSentId":121},{"question":"Why aren\u0027t there more Steve Jobses being created in America?","answer":"That is a great question.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":167,"aSentId":168},{"question":"What are the rules?","answer":"I want to come back and ask you how we get the uncertainty out of the game.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":186,"aSentId":187},{"question":"Do you share his faith, Jack?","answer":"With the right policies, certainly do.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":197,"aSentId":198},{"question":"What went so catastrophically wrong that meant that we had this terrible financial crisis?","answer":"So many things can be attributed to what caused the problem, but certainly lots of money available too easy.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":216,"aSentId":217},{"question":"Is that because greed kicks in?","answer":"No, I don\u0027t think it\u0027s so much greed.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":219,"aSentId":220},{"question":"Who was most to blame?","answer":"Boy, that\u0027s a hard one.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":228,"aSentId":229},{"question":"I mean, who were the main culprits here from a business perspective?","answer":"Well, I would have cleaned out anybody in the mortgage business who put faulty mortgages together.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":236,"aSentId":237},{"question":"Should some of these people have gone to jail?","answer":"I\u0027m not -- I\u0027m not qualified to pick that, whether that\u0027s true or not.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":241,"aSentId":242},{"question":"If you\u0027d been running Goldman Sachs, would you have allowed the multimillion dollar bonuses to be paid out after the bailout for the next few years?","answer":"Look, there\u0027s a culture in Wall Street, I own (INAUDIBLE) -- which is one of the worst moments in my life.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":263,"aSentId":264},{"question":"He said, this won\u0027t hurt my bonus, will it?","answer":"All he cared about.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":272,"aSentId":273},{"question":"Should they have done it?","answer":"Well, I mean --","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":290,"aSentId":291},{"question":"So I\u0027m not going to get drabbed into that one, OK?","answer":"But it\u0027s interesting that you even hesitate, because you\u0027ve been a big supporter previously, I\u0027ll grant you that, of allowing people to be paid what they should get in the marketplace.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":295,"aSentId":296},{"question":"It\u0027s wrong, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Seems to be.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":332,"aSentId":333},{"question":"When she says something like that, does it worry you she might have her finger on the nuclear trigger within a couple years?","answer":"I wouldn\u0027t support her for president.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":350,"aSentId":351},{"question":"You think she\u0027d be dangerous?","answer":"I just wouldn\u0027t support her for president.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":352,"aSentId":353},{"question":"Why not?","answer":"I don\u0027t think she has the gravitas or the international depth or a lot of things.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":354,"aSentId":355},{"question":"And you think it\u0027s because of that she\u0027s getting support?","answer":"Well, I mean, people follow her.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":359,"aSentId":360},{"question":"Do you see anybody emerging on the Republican side who is the kind of ladder that you\u0027re looking for?","answer":"You know, Piers, this is a great question, because if you asked me that a month ago, I would have said, well, Mitt Romney might be best guy, et cetera -- the most obvious guy.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":365,"aSentId":366},{"question":"I mean, you\u0027re a Republican, right?","answer":"Yes, absolutely.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":377,"aSentId":378},{"question":"But in your heart, do you think he can beat someone like Obama?","answer":"I\u0027m going to find out over the next 15 months -- hopefully, the next six to nine months because they\u0027re going to pick somebody in the primary.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":387,"aSentId":388},{"question":"Why do you think he\u0027s doing that?","answer":"He likes what he says.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":398,"aSentId":399},{"question":"When you look at countries like China, India, Brazil, so on, these emerging superpowers, economic powerhouses, how should America deal with this threat, which they\u0027ve never had to face before?","answer":"They ought to talk about them.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":439,"aSentId":440},{"question":"What is the right way to deal with China?","answer":"Out innovate them, which we can do, which we do all the time.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":467,"aSentId":468},{"question":"Do they scare you or excite you, the Chinese?","answer":"Excite me.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":476,"aSentId":477},{"question":"How do you feel about being a cute old dude, Jack?","answer":"I don\u0027t like the old part of it.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":497,"aSentId":498},{"question":"The trick is not to let anybody see then, right?","answer":"Hide them.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":540,"aSentId":541},{"question":"That true?","answer":"Something like that.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":555,"aSentId":556},{"question":"Not bad, is it?","answer":"For a kid from Salem that went through a 50 dollar a semester college, a hell of a country, huh.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":557,"aSentId":558},{"question":"Does money make you happy?","answer":"No.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":559,"aSentId":560},{"question":"Why isn\u0027t it recognizing that this is probably the big problem?","answer":"We\u0027re manufacturing lots of great -- we don\u0027t want to manufacture t-shirts.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":570,"aSentId":571},{"question":"What about, for example, very heavy big plant machinery and ship it to China, where they really need it?","answer":"We are.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":573,"aSentId":574},{"question":"Are we doing enough?","answer":"We\u0027re doing tons of it.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":576,"aSentId":577},{"question":"Isn\u0027t that where you could see real growth?","answer":"ELCH: We\u0027re seeing it.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":579,"aSentId":580},{"question":"Would you like to se more companies like that?","answer":"Of course we do.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":584,"aSentId":585},{"question":"Is that one of the answers, one of the solutions?","answer":"Yes, one of the solutions is that.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":586,"aSentId":587},{"question":"Are we getting enough of this ideology at the moment in America?","answer":"Yes, I think we are.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":613,"aSentId":614},{"question":"What\u0027s your experience of doing business with the Chinese?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s a -- they do it their way.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":639,"aSentId":640},{"question":"Were you surprised by the Warren Buffett affair recently, when his top guy had to leave in what were pretty unethical circumstances?","answer":"Warren will never understand that, nor will others.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":665,"aSentId":666},{"question":"Were you surprised that he allowed it to happen?","answer":"Warren runs a very decentralized company.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":670,"aSentId":671},{"question":"Do you think if you\u0027d been in his shoes and a top, top executive, running the show for you comes to you and says what that guy said to Warren Buffett, wouldn\u0027t alarm bells go off?","answer":"They did go off for Warren.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":676,"aSentId":677},{"question":"Do you enjoy your acting?","answer":"It was my big moment in the sun, I\u0027ll tell you.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":694,"aSentId":695},{"question":"Best businessman in the world right now?","answer":"One of them.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":706,"aSentId":707},{"question":"Who\u0027s been to you the most inspirational over all the years, all the business people you\u0027ve met?","answer":"Not one.","docId":"110608pmt","qSentId":709,"aSentId":710}]